{"TopicId":193044,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[KSP 1.8/1.9] Wild Blue Decals","CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-10T22:17:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-10T22:17:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Angel-125/Decals/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ELatest Release\u003C/a\u003E (Art assets license: All Rights Reserved)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Angel-125/Decals\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESource\u003C/a\u003E (License: GPLV3)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found myself wishing that I had an easy way to add decals to my craft to make them look better. I wanted something that would be easy to use, with no config files needed. With Wild Blue Decals, you can decorate your craft too!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wqsd5HF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wqsd5HF.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022304W9Cz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/304W9Cz.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223gxQHpM.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3gxQHpM.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Zlu52n9.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Zlu52n9.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Misguided Kerbal","CreatedById":203209,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-14T21:00:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is exactly what I needed, thank you so much! Does this happen to have a tweakscale plugin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(edit): Is this also compatible with 1.7?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-14T21:33:45Z\u0022 title=\u002204/14/2020 09:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Misguided_Kerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-15T00:58:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223770941\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586898012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203209\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Misguided_Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Misguided_Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is exactly what I needed, thank you so much! Does this happen to have a tweakscale plugin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(edit): Is this also compatible with 1.7?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might be compatible with KSP 1.7 but I don\u0027t know. There is currently no tweakscale support unless someone wants to make one. But there are other decal mods out there that do, I think. Their system is different.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-15T15:55:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771035\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586912313\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106975\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Angel-125\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Angel-125 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might be compatible with KSP 1.7 but I don\u0027t know. There is currently no tweakscale support unless someone wants to make one. But there are other decal mods out there that do, I think. Their system is different.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi! I tried this mod out. It is amazing! Only one thing. If I want to add my custom logo, what for format should it be in? And can it read flags outside the mods folder?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Weimaraner","CreatedById":203722,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-27T01:05:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771298\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586966142\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidCosmos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/16/2020 at 3:55 AM, VoidCosmos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi! I tried this mod out. It is amazing! Only one thing. If I want to add my custom logo, what for format should it be in? And can it read flags outside the mods folder?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the stock flags are 256x256 px, and the format should be png. I also recommend that your custom logo has a transparent background.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-27T07:14:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223776568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587949508\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203722\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Weimaraner\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Weimaraner said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the stock flags are 256x256 px, and the format should be png. I also recommend that your custom logo has a transparent background.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-27T15:08:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanx \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106975\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Angel-125\u003C/a\u003E for another great mod.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nWondering tho, if sizes are customizable, or we locked in to the default ones?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-27T15:48:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to bundle this with the In-Flight-Flag-Switcher mod I\u0027m trying to maintain, it would be a good fit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-27T16:22:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771298\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586966142\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidCosmos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/15/2020 at 8:55 AM, VoidCosmos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi! I tried this mod out. It is amazing! Only one thing. If I want to add my custom logo, what for format should it be in? And can it read flags outside the mods folder?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223776790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588000118\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277721\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stone Blue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Stone Blue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanx \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106975\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Angel-125\u003C/a\u003E for another great mod.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nWondering tho, if sizes are customizable, or we locked in to the default ones?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022304W9Cz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.50\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/304W9Cz.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSizes are limited to the stock 256 x 160 (1.6 : 1 aspect ratio) or 512 x 160 (3.2 : 1 aspect ratio) due to the parts. You can make textures bigger or smaller so long as they follow those two aspect ratios. It\u0027s a limitation of the UV mapping required for the parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223776807\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588002487\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to bundle this with the In-Flight-Flag-Switcher mod I\u0027m trying to maintain, it would be a good fit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTBH I had forgotten about the In-Flight-Flag-Switcher. Wild Blue Decals does allow both editor and in-flight flag switching, so if nothing else maybe the plugin will be of use to you \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UnhorsedGoose","CreatedById":199060,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-17T22:34:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo after reading the most recent \u0022KSP Loading...\u0022 post on Steam for KSP 1.10: Shared Horizons, it seems this mod will be made obsolete due to the addition of new Flag parts that are basically just this mod but slightly more fleshed out and are packaged with the stock game. Good to see this feature (finally) being added, and it\u0027ll mean you won\u0027t have to maintain this mod anymore! Unfortunately I\u0027m not sure the new parts will have a \u0027Wide\u0022 version for extra long flags but I could probably make do with a few normal-sized flags.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}